8545	[Push--pull over the {\v C}ech backbone is the product over intersection opens]
8546	  \label{lem:pushPull_sigma_iso}
8547	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.pushPull_sigma_iso, AlgebraicGeometry.pushPull_sigma_iso_π}
8548	  \uses{def:push_pull_obj, lem:cech_backbone_left_sigma, lem:pushPull_coprod_prod}
8549	  With the notation of Lemma~\ref{lem:cech_backbone_left_sigma}, the push--pull object on
8550	  the degree-\(p\) backbone decomposes as a product over the multi-indices:
8551	  \[
8552	    \operatorname{pushPullObj}\mathcal{F}\,Y_p
8553	      \;\cong\;
8554	    \prod_{\sigma : \mathrm{Fin}(p+1) \to I}
8555	      \operatorname{pushPullObj}\mathcal{F}\,(\operatorname{Over.mk} j_\sigma)
8556	    \qquad \text{in } X.\mathrm{Modules},
8557	  \]
8558	  equivalently \((q_p)_*\,(q_p)^*\mathcal{F} \cong \prod_\sigma (j_\sigma)_*\,
8559	  (j_\sigma)^*\mathcal{F}\).
8560	\end{lemma}
8561	\begin{proof}
8562	  \uses{lem:cech_backbone_left_sigma, lem:pushPull_coprod_prod}
8563	  By Lemma~\ref{lem:cech_backbone_left_sigma} the backbone \(Y_p\) is the coproduct
8564	  \(\coprod_\sigma U_\sigma\) with structure map \(q_p = \operatorname{Sigma.desc}(\sigma
8565	  \mapsto j_\sigma)\). Apply Lemma~\ref{lem:pushPull_coprod_prod} to this coproduct family,
8566	  with the finite multi-index type \(\sigma : \mathrm{Fin}(p+1) \to I\) as the index and the
8567	  intersection-open legs \(\operatorname{Over.mk} j_\sigma\), to obtain the asserted product
8568	  decomposition.
8569	\end{proof}
